Fallen Australian cricketer Phillip Hughes will be farewelled in a touching ceremony in his hometown of Macksville, with his father Greg, brother Jason and close friend Michael Clarke acting as pall bearers on Wednesday.

The five other pall bearers will be Corey Ireland, Mitchell Lonergan, Matthew Day, Aaron Finch and Tom Cooper - who was Hughes' batting partner at the time of last Tuesday's tragedy that claimed his life.

Devastated residents will get the chance to farewell their 'favourite son' as thousands of people from Australia and overseas inundate the 2,600-strong town in New South Wales.

