Before playing the 1974 hit, he added: 'This is for you Phil, wherever you are.'

Australian skipper Michael Clarke will also read a tribute during the service. 

Eulogies will be read by Nino Ramunno as sibilings Jason Hughes and Megan Hughes.

The service will be led by Father Michael Alcock.

Other sporting legends who will be attending include Shane Warne, Mike Hussey, Ricky Ponting, Glenn McGrath and Adam Gilchrist as well as the Australian Test squad and Commonwealth Bank Southern Stars.

Hughes' agent James Henderson told reporters the family wanted to stress that Wednesday's service was for the Macksville community and surrounding areas.

